# launch zellij with layout from `~/.config/zellij/layouts`
zellij --layout <layout name>

# Gotcha's
# https://zellij.dev/documentation/creating-a-layout.html?highlight=floating#global-cwd
1. global cwd only applies to the layout node itself
2. stacks are very buggy preset layouts.
  1. incompatible with horizontal splits
3. hide_floating_panes=true doesn't even seem to work?

1. ctrl-/ doesn't seem to work as a keybind???
2. ctrl-[ doesn't seem to work as a keybind???
... I think this is the case for most ctrl-<special> keys
... well maybe they work... they just can't be used to "Switch To" non-normal modes...

# Tips for flow
1. Use alt-/ to toggleterm instead of opening new panes
2. Use scrollback mode instead of scrolling with mouse
  3. Can select scrollback with <e> to open up nvim
4. If all else fails try opening another terminal terminal instance
